quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  25,1,"Blessed is He Who sent down on His servant the distinction (between right and wrong), that he may be a warner for the worlds"
  25,2,"He, Whose is the kingdom of the skies and the earth. And He has not taken (anyone as) a son, and He has no partner in the kingdom. And He created everything then programmed for it a programme"
  25,3,"And they have taken gods besides Him who do not create anything while they themselves are created, and they do not control (even) for themselves any harm or profit nor do they control death nor life, nor (do they have the power of) raising the dead (to life)"
  25,4,"And those who do not believe say, \"This is nothing but a lie which he has forged and other people have helped him at it.\" Thus they have come up with injustice and falsehood"
  25,5,"And they say, \"Stories of the ancient, which he has got written down as they are dictated to him morning and evening"
  25,6,"Say, \"He Who knows the secrets of the skies and the earth has sent it down. He is certainly Protectively Forgiving, Merciful"
  25,7,"And they say, \"What is (wrong with) this messenger, he eats food and walks in the markets? Why has not an angel been sent down to him so that he could be a warner along with him"
  25,8,"Or (why has not) a treasure been thrown down to him or (why is there no) garden for him from which he could eat?\" And those who are unjust say, \"You follow none but a man under the influence of magic"
  25,9,"See how they set forth similitude’s for you. Thus they have gone astray, therefore they will not be able to find the way"